    <title id="title">Consistent terminology</title>
    <abstract id="abstract"><shortdesc id="shortdesc">Define a term base that lists the terms and expressions to use in content</shortdesc>.
</abstract>
    <prolog id="prolog">
        <author id="author">France Baril</author>
        <publisher id="publisher">Architextus</publisher>
        <critdates id="critdates">
            <created id="created" date="2018-01-03"/>
        </critdates>
    </prolog>
    <body id="body">
        <p id="a0">Every organization should have a term base that spans across languages.</p>
        <p id="a1">The goal is simple:</p>
        <ul id="a2">
            <li id="a3">Use terms consistently</li>
            <li id="a4">Avoid the multiplication of synonyms</li>
        </ul>
        <p id="a5">The benefits are:</p>
        <ul id="a6">
            <li id="a7"><keypoint id="a8">Better user understanding</keypoint>. <p id="a9">Synonyms can confuse users who have to define each time if 1 or more features are discussed.</p></li>
            <li id="a10"><keypoint id="a11">Improve translation accuracy and efficiency</keypoint>. <p id="a12">The same term gets the same translation. </p></li>
        </ul>
        
    </body>
</topic>